  "business_context": "Solution / Knowledge Article records hold the institutional memory of customer-service organizations: the documented answers to \"how do I do X\" and \"what do I do when Y happens.\" The original Salesforce Solution object was simple — title, content, status, categories — and got superseded by a more capable Knowledge Article framework starting around 2014. Most modern Salesforce deployments use Knowledge rather than Solutions, but the Solution object still exists for legacy compatibility. Knowledge bases serve two audiences: internal agents (who reference articles to answer cases faster) and end customers (who self-serve via customer portals to deflect cases entirely). The case-deflection ROI is significant — published knowledge bases routinely deflect 20-40% of inbound case volume in mature deployments. When interviewing clients, surface \"Solution / Knowledge\" by asking whether they need to capture reusable answers to repeated customer questions, whether those answers should be searchable by agents, and whether they should be public-facing for customer self-service. Less universally available than Cases — Knowledge is a separately-licensed feature in many systems. Across the seven surveyed systems: Salesforce ships Solution (legacy) and Knowledge (modern); HubSpot has Knowledge Base (separate from CRM data model); EspoCRM has Knowledge Base; CiviCRM has no native concept; Attio has no native concept; NPSP follows Salesforce; Bloomerang has no concept.",
